Companion controller-input fixes for Vanilla-UI menus, layered on top of
companion-controller-nav.patch (applied LAST in the chain so its context matches the fully
patched ControllerManager::update()).

FIX 1 (generalized) — stuck movement/look after closing ANY pausing menu. While a menu is open a
held stick's RELEASE event is swallowed before reaching the ICS movement/look channels: by our
companionNavActive() block (DS overlays) OR by the vanilla `return !mGamepadGuiCursorEnabled`
deadzone branch in gamepadToGuiControl (any native menu — inventory/container/barter/dialogue/pause
— while the Game cursor is off). The channel stays deflected and the player keeps moving/looking on
close. The original FIX 1 only reset on a DS overlay close (companionNavActive true->false); this
generalizes it to fire on the GUI->gameplay transition (isGuiMode true->false), covering vanilla
menus, containers and the pause screen too. The companionConsumeResetAxes() path is kept (ORed in)
for the DS overlay->overlay case where GUI mode never drops.

FIX 3b — right-stick scroll of a Vanilla conversation (GM_Dialogue). Same problem/pattern as FIX 2
(GM_Scroll document reading): the native DialogueWindow exposes its history ScrollView via
getControllerScrollWidget(), but the native right-stick-scroll routing needs the game cursor, so
with the Game cursor OFF a held stick can't scroll it (and its value leaks into the look channel).
Poll the live right-stick Y and nudge the view directly. Gated on !companionNavActive() so it drives
ONLY the native (Vanilla) conversation — a DS conversation scrolls via COMPANION_NAV_SCROLL_* — and
on getMode() == GM_Dialogue so it never scrolls the history behind a service window pushed on top.

Kotlin: none. Native-only, no new externs. Verify markers: sWasGuiMode / leftGuiMode (FIX 1),
"FIX 3b" + sDlgScrollAccum (FIX 3b).
